news.title: Home First Finance Company India's net profit up 23.55% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Home First Finance Company India's total income stood at Rs 407.45 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 35.36 per cent from Rs 301.01 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: RR Kabel's net profit dips 3.35% in Q3 FY25
news.para: RR Kabel's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,795.59 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 9.10 per cent from Rs 1,645.76 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Indian commercial real estate to grow 5-6% year-on-year in FY26: Ind-Ra
news.para: New office supply is expected to decline to about 52 million sq ft in FY26.

news.title: Average office deal size in NCR rises 29% year-on-year in 2024: Knight Frank India
news.para: The average deal size for the commercial market across eight leading markets in the country has increased by 14% from 37,976 sq ft in 2023 to 43,387 sq ft in 2024.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to seek allocation of Rs 14,000 crore in Karnataka budget
news.para: While the civic body had presented a Rs 13,000-crore budget for 2024-25, this time it is expected to seek an allocation between Rs 13,000 crore and Rs 14,000 crore.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to revise land registration values from February 1
news.para: ​​The Minister explained that the revision would apply to areas that have developed as growth centers, where land prices are currently up to 10 times higher than the market value.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to demolish newly constructed building in Tangra
news.para: The KMC brass decided to demolish the newly constructed building first as advised by the KMC-empanelled structural engineer Snehasish Sinha, who submitted a report to the KMC authority based on his visit to the site and careful examination of the two buildings in Tangra.

news.title: The future of work: Exploring the long-term implications of flexible workspaces in India
news.para: As they look to adapt to a very different world of evolving working models, the flexible office segment emerged as a key differentiator.

news.title: UK rents outside London fall for first time since pandemic: Rightmove
news.para: The average advertised rent for new private-sector tenancies outside London fell by 0.2% in the final quarter of 2024 to 1,341 pounds ($1,672) per month. That was 4.7% higher than a year earlier, the smallest annual increase since 2021.

news.title: New home sales in US rise 3.6% in December 2024
news.para: The report from the Commerce Department on Monday also showed the rebound in home sales in November was much stronger than initially estimated.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body issues notices to 221 construction sites
news.para: The action was taken during its ongoing drive against construction firms after the civic body adopted the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) to combat pollution in the twin cities.

news.title: KMRL begins DPR process for metro phase III line connecting Aluva to Angamaly via airport
news.para: Procedures to appoint a DPR consultancy began after urban transport division of ministry of housing and urban affairs (MoHUA) granted in-principle approval for providing central financial assistance (CFA) for preparing DPR.

news.title: Odisha government to implement town planning scheme in Sambalpur and Rourkela
news.para: Housing and urban development minister Krushna Chandra Mahapatra on Monday held a high-level meeting with the various development authorities.

news.title: Omaxe to invest Rs 2,800 crore to develop projects under new brand
news.para: Omaxe's new brand will focus on joint ventures, collaboration and development through public-private partnerships (PPP).

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to develop 440 acre industrial park in Ahmedabad
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces' industrial park project has a total estimated area of about 440 acre and a top-line potential of Rs 1,350 crore.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to grant house sites only to BPL families
news.para: Special chief secretary (revenue) RP Sisodia on Monday released detailed guidelines for the implementation of ‘Housing for All' programme.

news.title: Saudi Arabia allows foreigners to invest in firms with property in Mecca and Medina
news.para: The move will allow foreigners to invest in firms whose revenues rely on the Islamic pilgrimage, one of the top revenue sources for the oil-rich kingdom.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body to collect Rs 200 crore from flat and plot owners in Vaishali
news.para: Among other proposals, the board deferred the implementation of mandatory structural audits for multi-storey buildings until discussions were held with members of Credai — an umbrella of developers.

news.title: Noida International airport set to launch on April 17
news.para: Officials said on Monday that the flooring of the terminal building is complete, and escalators and baggage handling systems have been installed.
